    "index.hero.tagline": "Specialty Coffee Brewing Guide",
    "index.hero.title1": "Master the Flow,",
    "index.hero.title2": "Unlock Ultimate Flavor",
    "index.hero.desc": "The soul of specialty pour-over coffee lies in precise rhythm and ratio. Barista Flow guides you through the professional '3-Stage Pour' technique, giving you perfect control over blooming, sweetness extraction, and strength.",
    "index.edu.title": "The Science of the 3-Stage Pour",
    "index.edu.subtitle": "How to balance acidity, sweetness, and body through precise timing and water flow.",
    "index.edu.step1.title": "1. Blooming",
    "index.edu.step1.desc": "Pour 2-2.5x the coffee weight in water to wet the grounds, wait ~40 seconds. This releases trapped CO2 (degassing), expanding the coffee bed and creating the perfect foundation for even extraction.",
    "index.edu.step2.title": "2. Main Extraction (Sweetness)",
    "index.edu.step2.desc": "The first major pour makes up 60% of total water. High temperature and steady circular pouring extract the bright fruit acids and sweet compounds. This stage determines the primary flavor balance.",
    "index.edu.step3.title": "3. Final Control (Strength)",
    "index.edu.step3.desc": "The final 40% adjusts the concentration. As water cools and most solubles are already extracted, switch to a gentle center pour or very soft circles to prevent over-extraction and woody bitterness.",
